Sunday evening somewhere on a hill near the curling banks of the river Rhein. A hall on top of that wineyard hill. A rowdy crowd has witnessed about 9 fabulous Amiga Demos, yet. Yeah, this is still the main event of the biggest pure scene parties. But the burner is still to come.

Ghandy and me were standing in the crowd starring at the bigscreen, sipping from the vodka....as just one of the typical loaderpictures by Louie showed up. Gosh, they finished it!

We heard during the past days that TBL had heavy troubles in finishing their production regarding to somewhat hardwarecrashes and more so that they've not shown up the days before at the party investing all time and nerves to complete the work at the hotel room.

µC3(Comment from Ghandy: Which exactly ten years ago also Dr. Jeckel & Mr. Hyde of Andromeda did, while they finished their work on the masterpiece "Nexus 7".)µC4

Ooops...even starting right now. That was a real short precalc time. I remember other TBL demos that took ages to allocate, decrunch etc....

The well known TBL logo appeared and so the show could start. Opening with minimalistic textscreens meshed up with bold fracture-letters leading to a big hall, which later can be recalled as an old fashioned terminal train station, where a huge clock is ticking ... count-clockwise!

So the well respected kings seem to turn back the time...let's see. Away from the backward ticking clock the view strays to a big door imediately opening and approaching the railroad platforms where just at the moment a train is arriving.

This whole scene comes like a dream in memory. It's just like you're old 'Noodles' in "Once Upon A Time In America" walking through the train station remembering the days as he became a young bootlegger.

So the colors well underline that feeling by giving the old antique photograph touch. And so the music does. At this moment µC5Blaizer`sµC4 tune is just spheric with plenty of echo and really slow beats. While the whole scene starts as a dream it ends right the same way.
Music calms down and the picture is fading to white.

And then the "Wake-up call". A 3D ballobject with great modeled distortions bouncing from one corner of the screen to the other right to the crunchy distorted beat the music goes now. Everybody woke up, yet?

The main beat starts...coming with a bold, slightly aggessiveness attitude so the crowd is forced to nod their heads ;D
